This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it focuses on Internet eXchange Points (IXPs) and their role in shaping the future Internet. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as IXPs are critical components of the Internet infrastructure and their security is of utmost importance. The paper also involves data analysis and comparisons, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on data collection and analysis could also place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category.
